sparql_query_kg2:
 Based on the provided context and mappings, here's the SPARQL query for Wikidata (KG2) to find all people who were born in Vienna and died in Berlin:

```sparql
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uri WHERE {
  ?uri wdt:P19 wd:Q1741 ;
       wdt:P20 ?deathPlace .
  VALUES ?deathPlace { wd:Q64 wd:Q31910788 wd:Q56036 wd:Q56037 }
}
```

This query uses the `PREFIX` declarations for Wikidata properties (`wdt:`) and entities (`wd:`). It selects distinct URIs (`?uri`) where the subject has Vienna (`wd:Q1741`) as the place of birth (`wdt:P19`) and one of the provided entities as the place of death (`wdt:P20`). The `VALUES` clause is used to include all possible death places mapped from DBpedia to Wikidata.

